  "For a linear transformation T: R^n -> R^m, the matrix representation A has what dimensions?": "",
  "m x m": "",
  "n x n": "",
  "m x n": "",
  "n x m": "",
  "An m x n matrix maps n-dimensional input vectors to m-dimensional output vectors. The number of rows equals the dimension of the codomain, and the number of columns equals the dimension of the domain.": "",
  "If A = [[1,2,3],[4,5,6]], what is A times the vector (1,0,0)?": "",
  "(6, 15)": "",
  "(1, 4)": "",
  "(2, 5)": "",
  "(1, 2, 3)": "",
  "Multiplying A by e1 = (1,0,0) simply extracts the first column of A: (1,4). This confirms that the columns of a transformation matrix are the images of the standard basis vectors.": "",
  "The zero transformation T(v) = 0 from R^2 to R^3 is represented by which matrix?": "",
  "A 2x2 zero matrix": "",
  "A 3x2 zero matrix": "",
  "A 3x3 zero matrix": "",
  "A 2x3 zero matrix": "",
  "The zero transformation from R^2 to R^3 needs a 3x2 matrix (m x n where m=3, n=2). Every entry is zero because T maps all vectors to the zero vector in R^3.": "",
  "If T: R^2 -> R^2 has matrix A = [[0,-1],[1,0]], what is T(3,4)?": "",
  "(4, -3)": "",
  "(3, -4)": "",
  "(-4, 3)": "",
